 Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above.JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Fikile Mbalula has appointed Yolisa Matakata as acting Hawks head.Matakata's appointment follows the removal as Berning Ntlemeza as Hawks head.Matakata was deputy Hawks head and previously Western Cape Hawks boss.Mbalula said he will appoint a permanent head by the end of 2017.On Wednesday, the North Gauteng High Court ruling ordered Ntlemeza to immediately vacate his office.READ: Berning Ntlemeza ordered to vacate Hawks positionThat s after it turned down his bid to appeal a previous ruling that his appointment was unlawful and unreasonable.The court also found that Ntlemeza had no hope of success in challenging its decision.Earlier, the minister s office withdrew its bid to appeal the court's decision against Ntlemeza.eNCA